SIMPLE: inflamed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inflamed
<hw>In*flamed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Set
on fire; enkindled; heated; congested; provoked; exasperated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Represented as burning, or as
adorned with tongues of flame.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Having an inflammation in; -- of
tissues; <as>as, an <ex>inflamed</ex> appendix</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inflamer</ent>⟦br⟧
